articles.title: What's new in TensorFlow 2.20
articles.summary: Posted by the TensorFlow team TensorFlow 2.20 has been released! For ongoing updates related to the multi-backend Keras, please note that all news and releases, starting with Keras 3.0, are now published directly on keras.io. You can find a complete list of all changes in the full release notes on GitHub. tf.lite is being replaced by LiteRT The tf.lite module will be deprecated with development for on-device inference moving to a new, independent repository: LiteRT.

articles.title: What's new in TensorFlow 2.19
articles.summary: Posted by the TensorFlow team TensorFlow 2.19 has been released! Highlights of this release include changes to the C++ API in LiteRT, bfloat16 support for tflite casting, discontinue of releasing libtensorflow packages.

articles.title: Introducing Wake Vision: A High-Quality, Large-Scale Dataset for TinyML Computer Vision Applications
articles.summary: Posted by Colby Banbury, Emil Njor, Andrea Mattia Garavagno, Vijay Janapa Reddi – Harvard University TinyML is an exciting frontier in machine learning, enabling models to run on extremely low-power devices such as microcontrollers and edge devices.

articles.title: MLSysBook.AI: Principles and Practices of Machine Learning Systems Engineering
articles.summary: Everyone wants to do the modeling work, but no one wants to do the engineering. If ML developers are like astronauts exploring new frontiers, ML systems engineers are the rocket scientists designing and building the engines that take them there.

articles.title: Roundtables: Why 2026 Is the Year for Sodium-Ion Batteries
articles.summary: Sodium-based batteries could be a cheaper, safer alternative to lithium-ion, and the technology is finally making its way into cars and energy storage arrays on the grid.

articles.title: A I-designed proteins may help spot cancer
articles.summary: Researchers at MIT and Microsoft have used artificial intelligence to create molecular sensors that could detect early signs of cancer via a urine test. The researchers developed an AI model to design short proteins targeted by enzymes called proteases, which are overactive in cancer cells.

articles.title: Salesforce CEO Marc Benioff: This isn't our first SaaSpocalypse
articles.summary: Salesforce reported a solid year-end earnings and then pulled out all the stops to ward off more talk of the death of its business to AI.

articles.title: Gushwork bets on AI search for customer leads — and early results are emerging
articles.summary: Gushwork has raised $9 million in a seed round led by SIG and Lightspeed. The startup has seen early customer traction from AI search tools like ChatGPT.

articles.title: Anthropic acquires computer-use AI startup Vercept after Meta poached one of its founders
articles.summary: Seattle-based Vercept developed complex agentic tools, including a computer-use agent that could complete tasks inside applications like a person with a laptop would.

articles.title: Nvidia has another record quarter amid record capex spends
articles.summary: "The demand for tokens in the world has gone completely exponential," Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang said about the company's earnings.

articles.title: The White House wants AI companies to cover rate hikes. Most have already said they would.
articles.summary: Many hyperscalers have already made public commitments to cover electricity cost increases.

articles.title: Alphabet-owned robotics software company Intrinsic joins Google
articles.summary: Nearly five years after graduating into an independent Alphabet company, Intrinsic is moving under Google's domain.

articles.title: The public opposition to AI infrastructure is heating up
articles.summary: Public backlash over the data center boom is leading to a variety of draconian policies — including bans on new construction.

articles.title: Gemini can now automate some multi-step tasks on Android
articles.summary: Gemini on Android will be able to automate tasks involving rideshare requests, or grocery or food delivery, says Google.

articles.title: OpenAI COO says ads will be 'an iterative process'
articles.summary: COO Brad Lightcap noted that ads can add to the product experience of users if they are done right.

articles.title: Trump claims tech companies will sign deals next week to pay for their own power supply
articles.summary: President Donald Trump tried to quell Americans' concerns about rising electricity costs during his State of the Union speech.

articles.title: Google and Samsung just launched the AI features Apple couldn't with Siri
articles.summary: Google just announced that Gemini will soon be able to take care of some multistep tasks on your phone, like ordering food or hailing a car, starting first with the Pixel 10 and the just-announced Samsung Galaxy S26 phones.

articles.title: Google Gemini can book an Uber or order food for you on Pixel 10 and Galaxy S26
articles.summary: Google's Gemini AI is getting one step closer to being more like an actual assistant. Starting with some Pixel 10 phones and the Samsung Galaxy S26 series, Gemini will be able to hail an Uber or put together a DoorDash order on its own.

articles.title: Amazon's AGI lab leader is leaving
articles.summary: After less than two years at Amazon, David Luan, the head of Amazon's San Francisco AI lab, is departing the company.

articles.title: Does Anthropic think Claude is alive? Define 'alive'
articles.summary: Over the past several weeks, as more and more Anthropic executives do interviews on a publicity blitz for Claude, one thing has gotten increasingly clear: Anthropic sure seems to think Claude is alive in some way, shape, or form.

articles.title: You can now make Alexa's AI personality more friendly, blunt, or chilled out
articles.summary: Amazon is giving you more control over how Alexa behaves during conversations and responses. Three personality style presets are launching today for Alexa Plus users in the US.

articles.title: Adobe's new AI video editing tool stitches clips into a first draft
articles.summary: Adobe is launching a new Firefly tool that helps video editors focus on storytelling by creating a first cut to refine and build around.

articles.title: Pete Hegseth's Pentagon AI bro squad includes a former Uber executive and a private equity billionaire
articles.summary: Hello and welcome to Regulator, covering the broligarchs, the influencers, and the potentially conscious artificial intelligence models scrambling for power in Washington.

articles.title: OpenAI defeats xAI's trade secrets lawsuit
articles.summary: OpenAI won a victory Tuesday in one of its legal battles with xAI, which involved allegations of poaching and theft of trade secrets. The former company's motion to dismiss the lawsuit was granted on Tuesday with leave to amend.

articles.title: Seedance 2.0 might be gen AI video's next big hope, but it's still slop
articles.summary: When Irish filmmaker Ruairi Robinson began uploading a series of short clips created with Seedance 2.0 - TikTok developer ByteDance's newest video generation model - it was hard to deny that the footage was much more impressive than what we've seen from other gen AI outfits.
